







       A CascadeButton should be used to post a PullDown Menu.
       This component must be composed of a button, with either a
       text or graphics label.  Following the label, this component
       should also include an arrow graphic, pointing in the direc-
       tion that the Menu will be posted to distinguish it from a
       PushButton.  The graphic is usually not shown in a MenuBar.














       A CascadeButton must have no internal navigation.  Cascade-
       Buttons follow the Menu activation model described in Sec-
       tion 2.3.3.  The following text describes the other opera-
       tions of this component.

